article.headline: Tennessee St. 71, Morehead St. 64
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Gerald Robinson Jr. scored 19 points to help Tennessee State hold off Morehead State 71-64 on Monday night. The Tigers (5-9, 3-1 Ohio Valley Conference) led by 17 points with 1:38 left in the first half, but the Eagles closed the gap to 37-28 by halftime. Morehead State (6-9, 3-1) rallied to tie the score twice in the second half, but could never take the lead. Parker Smith added 15 points and Jerrell Houston had 14 points and 12 rebounds for Tennessee State. Leon Buchanan led Morehead State with 19 points and eight rebounds and Robert Murry had 14 points. Kenneth Faried, the OVC Player of the Week, had his ninth double-double of the season with 11 points and 11 rebounds. Tennessee State won the rebounding battle 39-35 and made 5 of 11 3 pointers. Morehead State made 2 of 11 from beyond the arc.
